    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU1: Total knee arthroplasty tibial tray contact stress (Class II)",
    "description": "A finite element model is used to predict peak contact stress and stress distribution on the tibial tray of a TKA implant under physiological gait loading conditions. Model influence is MODERATE (model informs design margins alongside in vitro data); decision consequence is MODERATE (incorrect prediction could result in suboptimal implant geometry but clinical follow-up is available). Model Risk Level 3 per the Nagaraja assessment framework.",
    "intendedUse": "Use FE analysis to predict peak von Mises stress and contact pressure distribution on the tibial tray across five representative gait loading scenarios. Results must demonstrate stress levels below material fatigue threshold with uncertainty bounds. Requires mesh convergence study and sensitivity analysis on material properties.",
    "modelInfluence": "Moderate",
    "decisionConsequence": "Moderate",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
